"Ogasawara T., Débart A., Holzapfel M., Novák P., Bruce P.G.","Rechargeable Li2O2 electrode for lithium batteries",2006,"Journal of the American Chemical Society","128","4",,"1390","1393",,,10.1021/ja056811q,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-32044453597&partnerID=40&md5=f9e54840a0d77144cfb8c54569681ece","School of Chemistry, University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, Fife, KY16 9ST, United Kingdom; Electrochemistry Laboratory, Paul Scherrer Institut, CH-5232 Villigen PSI, Switzerland; Mobile Energy Company, SANYO Electric Co., Ltd., 7-3-2 Ibukidai-Higashimachi, Nishi-ku, Kobe, Hyogo, 651-2242, Japan","Ogasawara, T., School of Chemistry, University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, Fife, KY16 9ST, United Kingdom, Mobile Energy Company, SANYO Electric Co., Ltd., 7-3-2 Ibukidai-Higashimachi, Nishi-ku, Kobe, Hyogo, 651-2242, Japan; Débart, A., School of Chemistry, University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, Fife, KY16 9ST, United Kingdom; Holzapfel, M., Electrochemistry Laboratory, Paul Scherrer Institut, CH-5232 Villigen PSI, Switzerland; Novák, P., Electrochemistry Laboratory, Paul Scherrer Institut, CH-5232 Villigen PSI, Switzerland; Bruce, P.G., School of Chemistry, University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, Fife, KY16 9ST, United Kingdom","Rechargeable lithium batteries represent one of the most important developments in energy storage for 100 years, with the potential to address the key problem of global warming. However, their ability to store energy is limited by the quantity of lithium that may be removed from and reinserted into the positive intercalation electrode, LixCoO2, 0.5 &lt; x &lt; 1 (corresponding to 140 mA·h g-1 of charge storage). Abandoning the intercalation electrode and allowing Li to react directly with O2 from the air at a porous electrode increases the theoretical charge storage by a remarkable 5-10 times! Here we demonstrate two essential prerequisites for the successful operation of a rechargeable Li/O2 battery; that the Li2O2 formed on discharging such an O2 electrode is decomposed to Li and O2 on charging (shown here by in situ mass spectrometry), with or without a catalyst, and that charge/discharge cycling is sustainable for many cycles. © 2006 American Chemical Society.",,"Catalysts; Electrodes; Energy storage; Global warming; Mass spectrometry; Oxygen; Charge discharge cycling; Intercalation electrodes; Lithium batteries; lithium derivative; metal oxide; article; electric battery; electrochemistry; electrode; electronics; energy; mass spectrometry; X ray powder diffraction",,,,,,"Nazri, G.A., Pistoia, G., (2004) Lithium Batteries Science and Technology, , Kluwer Academic Publishers: MA; Schalkwijk, W.V., Scrosati, B., (2002) Advances in Lithium-Ion Batteries, , Kluwer Academic/Plenum Publishers: New York; Tarascon, J.-M., Armand, M., (2001) Nature, 414, pp. 359-367; Linden, D., (1984) Handbook of Batteries and Fuel Cells, , McGraw-Hill: New York; Visco, S.J., Nimon, E., Lithium metal aqueous batteries (2004) 12th International Meeting on Lithium Batteries, , Nara, Japan, June 27-July 2; Abstract 53; Abraham, K.M., Jiang, Z., (1996) J. Electrochem. Soc., 143, pp. 1-5; Dobley, A., Rodriguez, R., Abraham, K.M., High capacity cathodes for lithium-air batteries (2004) 206th Meeting of the Electrochemical Society, , Honolulu, HI, October 4-8; Abstract 496; Dobley, A., Morein, C., Abraham, K.M., Cathode optimization for lithium-air batteries (2005) 208th Meeting of the Electrochemical Society, , Los Angeles, CA, October 17; Abstract 823; Read, J., (2002) J. Electrochem. Soc., 149, pp. A1190-A1195; Read, J., Mutolo, K., Ervin, M., Behl, W., Wolfenstein, J., Drieger, A., Foster, D., (2003) J. Electrochem. Soc., 150, pp. A1351-A1356; Richard, M.N., Koetschau, I., Dahn, J.R., (1997) J. Electrochem. Soc., 144, pp. 554-557; Burchardt, T., (2004) J. Power Sources, 135, pp. 192-197; Tarascon, J.-M., Gozdz, A.S., Schmutz, C., Shokoohi, F., Warren, P.C., (1996) Solid State Ionics, 86-88, p. 49; Ufheil, J., Baertsch, C., Würsig, A., Novák, P., (2005) Electrochim. Acta, 50, pp. 1733-1738; Poizot, S., Laruelle, S., Grugeon, S., Dupont, L., Tarascon, J.-M., (2000) Nature, 407, pp. 496-499; Obrovac, M.N., Dunlap, R.A., Sanderson, R.J., Dahn, J.R., (2001) J. Electrochem. Soc., 148, pp. A576-A588; Kanamura, K., Okagawa, T., Takehara, Z., (1995) J. Power Sources, 57, pp. 119-123; Kuboki, T., Okuyama, T., Ohsaki, T., Takami, N., Lithium air batteries using hydrophobic room-temperature ionic liquid electrolyte (2004) 12th International Meeting on Lithium Batteries, , Nara, Japan, June 27-July 2; Abstract 398","Bruce, P.G.; School of Chemistry, University of St. Andrews, St. Andrews, Fife, KY16 9ST, United Kingdom; email: P.G.Bruce@st-andrews.ac.uk",,,,,,,,00027863,,JACSA,,"English","J. Am. Chem. Soc.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-32044453597
